                        </span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </li>
    <li id="comment-6343971" class="comment js-comment " data-comment-id="6343971" data-comment-owner-id="415763" data-comment-score="0">
        <div class="js-comment-actions comment-actions">
            <div class="comment-score js-comment-score js-comment-edit-hide">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-text  js-comment-text-and-form">
            <div class="comment-body js-comment-edit-hide">
                
                <span class="comment-copy">@Jorg Do you mean changing the whole WHILE loop to this?  while ($row = mysql_fetch_array($res)){ $results[] = $row;} Or just removing $result = new DALQueryResult(); and replacing with $results[] = $row; ?</span>
                
                <div class="d-inline-flex ai-center">
– <a href="/users/415763/stwhite" title="3,275 reputation" class="comment-user owner">stwhite</a>
                </div>
                <span class="comment-date" dir="ltr"><a class="comment-link" href="#comment6343971_5574869">
                    <span class="v-visible-sr">Commented</span>
                    <span title="2011-04-07 04:09:05Z, License: CC BY-SA 2.5" class="relativetime-clean">Apr 7, 2011 at 4:09</span>
                </a></span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </li>
    <li id="comment-6344336" class="comment js-comment " data-comment-id="6344336" data-comment-owner-id="502613" data-comment-score="0">
        <div class="js-comment-actions comment-actions">
            <div class="comment-score js-comment-score js-comment-edit-hide">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-text  js-comment-text-and-form">
            <div class="comment-body js-comment-edit-hide">
                
                <span class="comment-copy">replacing <code>while ($row = mysql_fetch_array($res)){ $result = new DALQueryResult(); foreach ($row as $k=&gt;$v){ $result-&gt;$k = $v; } $results[] = $result; } return $results;</code> with <code>while ($row = mysql_fetch_array($res)){ $results[] = $row; } return $results; </code> returns an array of arrays.</span>
                
                <div class="d-inline-flex ai-center">
– <a href="/users/502613/jorg" title="7,260 reputation" class="comment-user">Jorg</a>
