<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
        <div class="js-endorsements" data-for-answer="5575200">
</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>I take it you are using <a href="http://programmers.biz/programming/simple-php-class-based-querying" rel="nofollow">code that can be found here</a>. If so, just modify your SQL query with:</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php">ORDER BY relevancy, date
</code></pre>

<p>In your case it doesn't work because <code>DALQueryResult</code> is not an array, so <code>$v['relevancy']</code> will cause an error (it should be <code>$v-&gt;relevancy</code>). Even if you changed it, it wouldn't work because <code>DALQueryResult</code> is an object, not an array (and it doesn't implement <code>ArrayAccess</code> either).</p>

<p>I'd also suggest you use <a href="http://php.net/pdo" rel="nofollow">PDO</a> instead of a random class found on the web (if that's the case, of course). :)</p>
    </div>
