                        <li id="comment-6343346" class="comment js-comment " data-comment-id="6343346" data-comment-owner-id="415763" data-comment-score="0">
        <div class="js-comment-actions comment-actions">
            <div class="comment-score js-comment-score js-comment-edit-hide">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-text  js-comment-text-and-form">
            <div class="comment-body js-comment-edit-hide">
                
                <span class="comment-copy">Thanks for your answer. The reason why I'm looking for an alternate solution to using ORDER BY is because its a bigger strain on the database. By skipping ORDER BY in the query sorting in PHP the processing time would be faster.   So if the function I've listed in my question doesn't work with this, is there another option to sort the array—without using PDO or ORDER BY?</span>
                
                <div class="d-inline-flex ai-center">
– <a href="/users/415763/stwhite" title="3,275 reputation" class="comment-user owner">stwhite</a>
                </div>
                <span class="comment-date" dir="ltr"><a class="comment-link" href="#comment6343346_5575200">
                    <span class="v-visible-sr">Commented</span>
