    </li>
    <li id="comment-6343433" class="comment js-comment " data-comment-id="6343433" data-comment-owner-id="492901" data-comment-score="0">
        <div class="js-comment-actions comment-actions">
            <div class="comment-score js-comment-score js-comment-edit-hide">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-text  js-comment-text-and-form">
            <div class="comment-body js-comment-edit-hide">
                
                <span class="comment-copy">@stwhite: MySQL has been built to handle tasks such as ordering result sets. It will be faster to sort in MySQL than PHP most of the times (if not all). Even faster if your fields are indexed. Not to mention query cache and scaling. You shouldn't worry about the database server load for such a trivial task.</span>
                
                <div class="d-inline-flex ai-center">
– <a href="/users/492901/netcoder" title="67,845 reputation" class="comment-user">netcoder</a>
                </div>
                <span class="comment-date" dir="ltr"><a class="comment-link" href="#comment6343433_5575200">
                    <span class="v-visible-sr">Commented</span>
                    <span title="2011-04-07 02:52:22Z, License: CC BY-SA 2.5" class="relativetime-clean">Apr 7, 2011 at 2:52</span>
                </a></span>
                        <span title="this comment was edited 1 time">
                            <svg aria-hidden="true" class="va-text-bottom o50 svg-icon iconPencilSm" width="14" height="14" viewbox="0 0 14 14"><path fill="#F1B600" d="m2 10.12 6.37-6.43 1.88 1.88L3.88 12H2z"/><path fill="#E87C87" d="m11.1 1.71 1.13 1.12c.2.2.2.51 0 .71L11.1 4.7 9.21 2.86l1.17-1.15c.2-.2.51-.2.71 0"/></svg>
                        </span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </li>
    <li id="comment-6343443" class="comment js-comment " data-comment-id="6343443" data-comment-owner-id="492901" data-comment-score="0">
        <div class="js-comment-actions comment-actions">
            <div class="comment-score js-comment-score js-comment-edit-hide">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="comment-text  js-comment-text-and-form">
            <div class="comment-body js-comment-edit-hide">
                
                <span class="comment-copy">@stwhite: If you really want to sort from a PHP object using <code>array_multisort</code>, you will have to have it implement <a href="http://php.net/ArrayAccess" rel="nofollow noreferrer">ArrayAccess</a>.</span>
                
                <div class="d-inline-flex ai-center">
– <a href="/users/492901/netcoder" title="67,845 reputation" class="comment-user">netcoder</a>
